verses.text: These \add are\add* the \w journeys|strong="H4550"\w* of the \w children|strong="H1121"\w* of \w Israel|strong="H3478"\w*, which went \w forth|strong="H3318"\w* out of the \w land|strong="H0776"\w* of \w Egypt|strong="H4714"\w* with their \w armies|strong="H6635"\w* under the \w hand|strong="H3027"\w* of \w Moses|strong="H4872"\w* and \w Aaron|strong="H0175"\w*.

And \w Moses|strong="H4872"\w* \w wrote|strong="H3789"\w* their goings \w out|strong="H4161"\w* according to their \w journeys|strong="H4550"\w* by the \w commandment|strong="H6310"\w* of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*: and these \add are\add* their \w journeys|strong="H4550"\w* according to their goings \w out|strong="H4161"\w*.

And they \w departed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Rameses|strong="H7486"\w* in the \w first|strong="H7223"\w* \w month|strong="H2320"\w*, on the \w fifteenth|strong="H6240"\w* \w day|strong="H3117"\w* of the \w first|strong="H7223"\w* \w month|strong="H2320"\w*; on the \w morrow|strong="H4283"\w* after the \w passover|strong="H6453"\w* the \w children|strong="H1121"\w* of \w Israel|strong="H3478"\w* went \w out|strong="H3318"\w* with an \w high|strong="H7311"\w* \w hand|strong="H3027"\w* in the \w sight|strong="H5869"\w* of all the \w Egyptians|strong="H4714"\w*.

For the \w Egyptians|strong="H4714"\w* \w buried|strong="H6912"\w* all \add their\add* \w firstborn|strong="H1060"\w*, which the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* had \w smitten|strong="H5221"\w* among them: upon their \w gods|strong="H0430"\w* also the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* \w executed|strong="H6213"\w* \w judgments|strong="H8201"\w*.
And the \w children|strong="H1121"\w* of \w Israel|strong="H3478"\w* \w removed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Rameses|strong="H7486"\w*, and \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* in \w Succoth|strong="H5523"\w*.

And they \w departed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Succoth|strong="H5523"\w*, and \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* in \w Etham|strong="H0864"\w*, which \add is\add* in the \w edge|strong="H7097"\w* of the \w wilderness|strong="H4057"\w*.

And they \w removed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Etham|strong="H0864"\w*, and turned \w again|strong="H7725"\w* unto \w Pi-hahiroth|strong="H6367"\w*, which \add is\add* before \w Baal-zephon|strong="H1189"\w*: and they \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* \w before|strong="H6440"\w* \w Migdol|strong="H4024"\w*.

And they \w departed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w before|strong="H6440"\w* \w Pi-hahiroth|strong="H6367"\w*, and passed \w through|strong="H5674"\w* the \w midst|strong="H8432"\w* of the \w sea|strong="H3220"\w* into the \w wilderness|strong="H4057"\w*, and \w went|strong="H3212"\w* \w three|strong="H7969"\w* \w days’|strong="H3117"\w* \w journey|strong="H1870"\w* in the \w wilderness|strong="H4057"\w* of \w Etham|strong="H0864"\w*, and \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* in \w Marah|strong="H4785"\w*.

And they \w removed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Marah|strong="H4785"\w*, and \w came|strong="H0935"\w* unto \w Elim|strong="H0362"\w*: and in \w Elim|strong="H0362"\w* \add were\add* \w twelve|strong="H8147"\w* \w fountains|strong="H5869"\w* of \w water|strong="H4325"\w*, and threescore and \w ten|strong="H7657"\w* palm \w trees|strong="H8558"\w*; and they \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* there.
And they \w removed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Elim|strong="H0362"\w*, and \w encamped|strong="H2583"\w* by the \w Red|strong="H5488"\w* \w sea|strong="H3220"\w*.
And they \w removed|strong="H5265"\w* from the \w Red|strong="H5488"\w* \w sea|strong="H3220"\w*, and \w encamped|strong="H2583"\w* in the \w wilderness|strong="H4057"\w* of \w Sin|strong="H5512"\w*.
And they took their \w journey|strong="H5265"\w* out of the \w wilderness|strong="H4057"\w* of \w Sin|strong="H5512"\w*, and \w encamped|strong="H2583"\w* in \w Dophkah|strong="H1850"\w*.
And they \w departed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Dophkah|strong="H1850"\w*, and \w encamped|strong="H2583"\w* in \w Alush|strong="H0442"\w*.

And they \w removed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Alush|strong="H0442"\w*, and \w encamped|strong="H2583"\w* at \w Rephidim|strong="H7508"\w*, where was no \w water|strong="H4325"\w* for the \w people|strong="H5971"\w* to \w drink|strong="H8354"\w*.
And they \w departed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Rephidim|strong="H7508"\w*, and \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* in the \w wilderness|strong="H4057"\w* of \w Sinai|strong="H5514"\w*.

And they \w removed|strong="H5265"\w* from the \w desert|strong="H4057"\w* of \w Sinai|strong="H5514"\w*, and \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* at \w Kibroth-hattaavah|strong="H6914"\w*.\f + \fr 33.16 \ft Kibroth-hattaavah: that is, the graves of lust\f*
And they \w departed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Kibroth-hattaavah|strong="H6914"\w*, and \w encamped|strong="H2583"\w* at \w Hazeroth|strong="H2698"\w*.
And they \w departed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Hazeroth|strong="H2698"\w*, and \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* in \w Rithmah|strong="H7575"\w*.
And they \w departed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Rithmah|strong="H7575"\w*, and \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* at \w Rimmon-parez|strong="H7428"\w*.
And they \w departed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Rimmon-parez|strong="H7428"\w*, and \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* in \w Libnah|strong="H3841"\w*.
And they \w removed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Libnah|strong="H3841"\w*, and \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* at \w Rissah|strong="H7446"\w*.
And they \w journeyed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Rissah|strong="H7446"\w*, and \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* in \w Kehelathah|strong="H6954"\w*.
And they \w went|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Kehelathah|strong="H6954"\w*, and \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* in \w mount|strong="H2022"\w* \w Shapher|strong="H8234"\w*.
And they \w removed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w mount|strong="H2022"\w* \w Shapher|strong="H8234"\w*, and \w encamped|strong="H2583"\w* in \w Haradah|strong="H2732"\w*.
And they \w removed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Haradah|strong="H2732"\w*, and \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* in \w Makheloth|strong="H4722"\w*.
And they \w removed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Makheloth|strong="H4722"\w*, and \w encamped|strong="H2583"\w* at \w Tahath|strong="H8480"\w*.
And they \w departed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Tahath|strong="H8480"\w*, and \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* at \w Tarah|strong="H8646"\w*.
And they \w removed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Tarah|strong="H8646"\w*, and \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* in \w Mithcah|strong="H4989"\w*.
And they \w went|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Mithcah|strong="H4989"\w*, and \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* in \w Hashmonah|strong="H2832"\w*.
And they \w departed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Hashmonah|strong="H2832"\w*, and \w encamped|strong="H2583"\w* at \w Moseroth|strong="H4149"\w*.
And they \w departed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Moseroth|strong="H4149"\w*, and \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* in \w Bene-jaakan|strong="H1142"\w*.
And they \w removed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Bene-jaakan|strong="H1142"\w*, and \w encamped|strong="H2583"\w* at \w Hor-hagidgad|strong="H2735"\w*.
And they \w went|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Hor-hagidgad|strong="H2735"\w*, and \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* in \w Jotbathah|strong="H3193"\w*.
And they \w removed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Jotbathah|strong="H3193"\w*, and \w encamped|strong="H2583"\w* at \w Ebronah|strong="H5684"\w*.
And they \w departed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Ebronah|strong="H5684"\w*, and \w encamped|strong="H2583"\w* at \w Ezion-gaber|strong="H6100"\w*.

And they \w removed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Ezion-gaber|strong="H6100"\w*, and \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* in the \w wilderness|strong="H4057"\w* of \w Zin|strong="H6790"\w*, which \add is\add* \w Kadesh|strong="H6946"\w*.

And they \w removed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Kadesh|strong="H6946"\w*, and \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* in \w mount|strong="H2022"\w* \w Hor|strong="H2023"\w*, in the \w edge|strong="H7097"\w* of the \w land|strong="H0776"\w* of \w Edom|strong="H0123"\w*.

And \w Aaron|strong="H0175"\w* the \w priest|strong="H3548"\w* went \w up|strong="H5927"\w* into \w mount|strong="H2022"\w* \w Hor|strong="H2023"\w* at the \w commandment|strong="H6310"\w* of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, and \w died|strong="H4191"\w* there, in the \w fortieth|strong="H0705"\w* \w year|strong="H8141"\w* after the \w children|strong="H1121"\w* of \w Israel|strong="H3478"\w* were come \w out|strong="H3318"\w* of the \w land|strong="H0776"\w* of \w Egypt|strong="H4714"\w*, in the \w first|strong="H0259"\w* \add day\add* of the \w fifth|strong="H2549"\w* \w month|strong="H2320"\w*.

And \w Aaron|strong="H0175"\w* \add was\add* an \w hundred|strong="H3967"\w* and \w twenty|strong="H6242"\w* and \w three|strong="H7969"\w* \w years|strong="H8141"\w* \w old|strong="H1121"\w* when he \w died|strong="H4194"\w* in \w mount|strong="H2022"\w* \w Hor|strong="H2023"\w*.

And \w king|strong="H4428"\w* \w Arad|strong="H6166"\w* the \w Canaanite|strong="H3669"\w*, which \w dwelt|strong="H3427"\w* in the \w south|strong="H5045"\w* in the \w land|strong="H0776"\w* of \w Canaan|strong="H3667"\w*, \w heard|strong="H8085"\w* of the \w coming|strong="H0935"\w* of the \w children|strong="H1121"\w* of \w Israel|strong="H3478"\w*.
And they \w departed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w mount|strong="H2022"\w* \w Hor|strong="H2023"\w*, and \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* in \w Zalmonah|strong="H6758"\w*.
And they \w departed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Zalmonah|strong="H6758"\w*, and \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* in \w Punon|strong="H6325"\w*.
And they \w departed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Punon|strong="H6325"\w*, and \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* in \w Oboth|strong="H0088"\w*.

And they \w departed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Oboth|strong="H0088"\w*, and \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* in \w Ije-abarim|strong="H5863"\w*, in the \w border|strong="H1366"\w* of \w Moab|strong="H4124"\w*.\f + \fr 33.44 \ft Ije-abarim: or, heaps of Abarim\f*
And they \w departed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Iim|strong="H5864"\w*, and \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* in \w Dibon-gad|strong="H1769"\w*.
And they \w removed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Dibon-gad|strong="H1769"\w*, and \w encamped|strong="H2583"\w* in \w Almon-diblathaim|strong="H5963"\w*.

And they \w removed|strong="H5265"\w* from \w Almon-diblathaim|strong="H5963"\w*, and \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* in the \w mountains|strong="H2022"\w* of \w Abarim|strong="H5682"\w*, \w before|strong="H6440"\w* \w Nebo|strong="H5015"\w*.

And they \w departed|strong="H5265"\w* from the \w mountains|strong="H2022"\w* of \w Abarim|strong="H5682"\w*, and \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* in the \w plains|strong="H6160"\w* of \w Moab|strong="H4124"\w* by \w Jordan|strong="H3383"\w* \add near\add* \w Jericho|strong="H3405"\w*.

And they \w pitched|strong="H2583"\w* by \w Jordan|strong="H3383"\w*, from \w Beth-jesimoth|strong="H1020"\w* \add even\add* unto \w Abel-shittim|strong="H0063"\w* in the \w plains|strong="H6160"\w* of \w Moab|strong="H4124"\w*.\f + \fr 33.49 \ft Abel-shittim: or, the plains of Shittim\f*

¶ And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \w spake|strong="H1696"\w* unto \w Moses|strong="H4872"\w* in the \w plains|strong="H6160"\w* of \w Moab|strong="H4124"\w* by \w Jordan|strong="H3383"\w* \add near\add* \w Jericho|strong="H3405"\w*, \w saying|strong="H0559"\w*,

\w Speak|strong="H1696"\w* unto the \w children|strong="H1121"\w* of \w Israel|strong="H3478"\w*, and \w say|strong="H0559"\w* unto them, When ye are passed \w over|strong="H5674"\w* \w Jordan|strong="H3383"\w* into the \w land|strong="H0776"\w* of \w Canaan|strong="H3667"\w*;

Then ye shall drive \w out|strong="H3423"\w* all the \w inhabitants|strong="H3427"\w* of the \w land|strong="H0776"\w* from \w before|strong="H6440"\w* you, and \w destroy|strong="H0006"\w* all their \w pictures|strong="H4906"\w*, and \w destroy|strong="H0006"\w* all their \w molten|strong="H4541"\w* \w images|strong="H6754"\w*, and quite pluck \w down|strong="H8045"\w* all their high \w places|strong="H1116"\w*:

And ye shall \w dispossess|strong="H3423"\w* \add the inhabitants\add* of the \w land|strong="H0776"\w*, and \w dwell|strong="H3427"\w* therein: for I have \w given|strong="H5414"\w* you the \w land|strong="H0776"\w* to \w possess|strong="H3423"\w* it.

And ye shall \w divide|strong="H5157"\w* the \w land|strong="H0776"\w* by \w lot|strong="H1486"\w* for an \w inheritance|strong="H5157"\w* among your \w families|strong="H4940"\w*: \add and\add* to the \w more|strong="H7227"\w* ye shall give the \w more|strong="H7235"\w* \w inheritance|strong="H5159"\w*, and to the \w fewer|strong="H4592"\w* ye shall give the \w less|strong="H4591"\w* \w inheritance|strong="H5159"\w*: every man’s \add inheritance\add* shall be in the place where his \w lot|strong="H1486"\w* \w falleth|strong="H3318"\w*; according to the \w tribes|strong="H4294"\w* of your \w fathers|strong="H0001"\w* ye shall \w inherit|strong="H5157"\w*.\f + \fr 33.54 \ft give the more…: Heb. multiply his inheritance\f*\f + \fr 33.54 \ft give the less…: Heb. diminish his inheritance\f*

But if ye will not drive \w out|strong="H3423"\w* the \w inhabitants|strong="H3427"\w* of the \w land|strong="H0776"\w* from \w before|strong="H6440"\w* you; then it shall come to pass, that those which ye let \w remain|strong="H3498"\w* of them \add shall be\add* \w pricks|strong="H7899"\w* in your \w eyes|strong="H5869"\w*, and \w thorns|strong="H6796"\w* in your \w sides|strong="H6654"\w*, and shall \w vex|strong="H6887"\w* you in the \w land|strong="H0776"\w* wherein ye \w dwell|strong="H3427"\w*.
Moreover it shall come to pass, \add that\add* I shall \w do|strong="H6213"\w* unto you, as I \w thought|strong="H1819"\w* to \w do|strong="H6213"\w* unto them.
